Sleep Apnea:

• Sleep apnea is a condition in which one stops breathing briefly, while asleep
• It occurs due to a blockage in the respiratory tract 

Symptoms to look for:

• Bad sleep
• Waking up gasping for breath
• Snoring
• Dry throat
• Headache on waking up

